##Some reasons why riders fall in love with Wuhan | Wuhan Wuhan

I'm Claire Kuo, the reporter.

I saw old timer on the street for the first time one day. For some reason, the first time I met him, I thought he had a story. He's not old. He's a post-'80s kid. But chat up, you can easily find him on the world of human insight, little experience, is very difficult to penetrate.

In fact, he did the same thing when there was no outbreak, but he had only 40 followers then, and now he has more than 69,000.

Old Man with a story. What's been going on these days? Late One night, he told his story this way.

1

Last June, I came to Wuhan as a rider

My name is Wu Hui. I'm 39 years old. I'm actually 40.

Many years ago I studied in Wuhan, four years of college. I don't want to embarrass the school. Many years later, I returned to Wuhan after my business failed. Although I always said Wuhan is not good, but in the end I chose to work in Wuhan. Because there is a special feeling to Wuhan.

I went to Wuhan in June last year and became a rider in July. I have been riding ever since. There are several reasons why I came to Wuhan as a horseman.

I was failing in my business, and I was at an all-time low, and for a year or two, I felt like I wasn't succeeding at anything, that I was in total denial, that I was in a bad state of mind.

But then one day, I realized it wasn't gonNA work. I'm trying to change. I have to change. The first thing to change is your environment, which is relatively easy to do, because you can't suddenly make a big change in your situation. Well, first of all, I changed cities and jobs. I thought of Wuhan at that time.

Then why ride? Because I needed to reach out to more people. The job of a rider, although it may be physically tiring to run alone every day, is psychologically satisfying. I thought it would be good for me, help me get out of it, so here I am.

Second, I heard it's more free, and I make a lot of money. Riders make good money. If you work a little harder, you can beat the average income in Wuhan.

Well, another reason is that, although I sometimes have a bit of a bad temper, and I have a lot of soft spots, it's easier for me to think from someone else's point of view, for example, with whom I have a disagreement, to put yourself in someone else's shoes.

If you have to say that I have some special skills, may be a little bit on the text, because I grew up reading, reading a lot of books, also wrote a lot of things, although not professional, but some sensitivity to the text.

2

Twenty years ago, orders for face masks were particularly high

It was raining all those days years ago. It was cloudy and rainy all the time. January 20th, I didn't feel anything. Then on the evening of the 20th, Academician Zhong Nanshan gave a speech.

I finished work early that day, about 11 o'clock to go back, so saw Zhong Nanshan said, that night can be confirmed will pass from person to person, also in the appeal to wear a mask.

There were three of us in the room, and one of the guys came home late from work, and he got home around 12:00, and he was already wearing a mask. I asked him, "where did you get the mask? " And he told me.

The next morning I started working normally, and around 10:00 I went to the place where he said you can't buy masks anymore. On the 21st, I ran 38 deals, and a lot of them were convenience store deals. Usually, the order of the convenience store is not much, a little more in the evening, it is to buy beer and so on. But on the 21st, the list at the convenience store was unusually large.

There is a very inconspicuous convenience store, usually may be a few dozen a day, but the order that day is too much, about noon is already more than 200 single, the whole day is more than 600 single seems, very terrible!

I also had an order for a convenience store that day, another chain called Miyako. I looked, and it was full of masks! Every order comes with a face mask, and one from as far away as the states.

I got an order. He's in the states, and he wants me to run an errand for him to buy a mask. N95. It was no longer available. I said, I'm sorry, you can't buy this anymore. It's just a surgical mask. He said it was a surgical mask, and he said he was overseas, and he wanted me to take it wherever he could.

I went a long way to get that one. It was like four miles. When we got there, I saw only boxes, 30 a box, 60 bucks a box. He said that's fine, that's fine. He wants a box. But I bought four boxes, sent him one, kept three for myself, and I still haven't used them all.

On the way to deliver food, I saw a large number of people shopping, they pull the usual food carts, are full. Rice, instant noodles, oil, what mess have, too much to take, you see those uncles lifted Chi Chi, Gasp. You don't usually see people buying this much stuff. There were a lot of people on the road.

3

New Year's first order,

A concerned citizen ordered me to take it to Wuchang Hospital

To be exact, there was a noticeable change of events on the 24th, the 30th of this year.

In the early morning of the 23rd, I got the news of the "closing of the city" . In the morning, I contacted my brother and nephew. My brother was on the 8:00 a.m. train home on the 23rd, and he said he'd be here soon. I told him what I know about the situation, I said you pay attention to a little bit, do not always go back to gather. Where I come from, there are many families. If you get together, you can gather more than 20 people for dinner.

After work on the 23rd, I decided to take a day off on the 24th because I was tired. The 24th is also the first day of our new mission cycle, and there is plenty of time to complete the order tasks later. No Rush. And the other one, I'm a little scared, too, and I'm kind of drumming. Of course, there is another reason: Thirty Children's New Year!

Things you don't have time to think about during the day, things you don't have time to think about at night. It's only during breaks that you have time to really think about what state we're in, myself included, and the epidemic, and I have to make an assessment in my mind. I look at all kinds of authoritative sources, and then I look at twitter, and you see that this is something you've never seen before.

Because I also like history, I know, in some big historical events, the fate of the individual is hard to tell.

First of all, of course, to worry about myself, and then I went to look at all the information, to assess what the virus was, and after looking at it a lot, I found that it didn't have to be so scary, and I was a little relieved.

The job still needs to be done. A few thousand dollars is very important to me. Originally the Spring Festival is to earn money to stay here, and then you rest and quit? So the next day, the first day of the New Year, I was back at work.

The other reason is that I want to go out and see if it's really happening out there?

Because on the 30th day, I saw information flying all over the place. I saw the doctors who ate instant noodles. I knew that medical care was absolutely the first line, Eh. It was a bit uncomfortable to see them eating instant noodles. I said I would go to the hospital to have a look. I went to the Wuchang Hospital, and then South Central Hospital.

It was a quiet day at central South Hospital, and I don't know why, but there was nothing out of the ordinary or anything that made me nervous. Going to the Wuchang Hospital is a little bit stressful, Wuchang Hospital has a lot of people in and out, a lot of cars, everyone is very busy, but also did not see any other out of the ordinary.

The first order of the New Year was sent to the Wuchang Hospital by the warm-hearted citizens. I ordered a lot. It's expensive. About 10 of them. Five hundred bucks. He should have asked me to send him to Liyuan Health Service Center under Wuchang Hospital, but he wrote wrong and put "Wuchang Hospital outpatient department. ". So I went back to the Pear Garden Health Service, and a young man came out to get it.

After the delivery, I was a little thirsty, to the next store to buy a water turned to drink, and then chat with the boss. The boss asked me where to send it? I said sideways. He says it's the community health service at Wuchang Hospital, and it's usually the hospital service that cooks for them, and they don't deliver for days.

May Be the Spring Festival Wuchang Hospital Logistics Force was insufficient, and suddenly encountered the epidemic. Wuchang Hospital is a designated treatment hospital, so they themselves may not be able to solve the problem of eating, not to mention the health services below, no food is normal.

I went by Wuchang Hospital a bunch of times. I don't remember the exact time. I had just arrived at Wuchang Hospital, and there was an ambulance at the door, the back door of the ambulance was open, and there was a stretcher, half in the car, half out. A doctor-looking man was doing compressions. I don't know if he was a doctor or a nurse. He was wearing a blue hat and white clothes. Not a lab coat, but it's not a hazmat suit. I don't know if he's doing CPR, like...

4

"Mama's cooking for Papa,

My Dad is a front-line doctor. Thank you!"

I finished work early that day because I finished the task. It was around 5:00, so I went home to rest and get ready for dinner.

We didn't eat out for a few days. First, we didn't feel safe. Second, there was nothing to eat. I always cook noodles in hot pot.

I finished washing, sitting on the bed ready to brush micro-blog, and then to charge the phone, I used this broken cell phone, did not use more than a short period of time before the battery.

Even after work, we used to look at the list. The MEITUAN lobby has all kinds of lists you can grab. That day that list is in the first row, I read a note to write is: "My mother cooked food to my father, my father is a front-line doctor. Thanks brother! "

I took it! I didn't even think about it.

The girl lives in our neighborhood, not far from here, says her dad's in a hotel, a doctor. I went downstairs to call the girl, and she said her dad was all over the place.

To the hotel, out of a person, I said, "you are Dr. Chen? " He said No. I froze, take the order to show him, I said, "you see the family entrusted me to bring dinner to Dr. Chen. ". Then he said, he next door 802 is Dr. Chen, but Dr. Chen went back to the hospital, let me put his colleagues. It just so happens that door 802, also a male doctor, was open.

On the way back, I hit "delivery" on my APP and couldn't find it. This order requires the recipient to acknowledge receipt and give you a 4-digit code that you type in to Click "delivery. ". But since I didn't see him in person, there's no receipt code.

I had to call the girl who placed the order. I said you wait for me, I can APP operation, let the receipt code again, you can complete the order.

We started talking on the APP, and she said, "thank you very much. This is a serious epidemic, so be careful, " she added, "It's very admirable of you to be working out at this hour, and I thank you very much, " he said, especially politely.

I replied, "thanks to people like your father. "

And you can feel the pride in what that girl said, about having a doctor's dad out there. I'm jealous, you know? It's not envy. It's jealousy.

A long time later, someone sent me a private message on Weibo, saying, "I finally found you. Finally. I'm the girl. "

5

What does fresh hot and dry noodles mean?

One day, someone wrote me a message on Weibo saying, "can you buy me some medicine? " So I asked where she was. A question, very close, in the lake (north) university (university) opposite.

The medicine she asked for was Nin Jiom Pei PA Koa so she could buy it. If what Oseltamivir, even flowers Qingwen more difficult to buy. I said, "No, it's fine. " The next day I bought it for her, and then I went on another trip.

Then she sent me a wechat message: "could you buy Oseltamivir and Lianhua Qingwen Capsule for me this afternoon? " I said, "yes, no problem! "

I had to help her look again. I seem to remember where they were sold, but I'm not sure which pharmacy. And then I'm GONNA walk around and I'm GonNa go to the drugstore. Before I could get it, she said she wanted to buy some more Amoxicillin, but I forgot it when I bought it. I bought Oseltamivir and Lianhua Qingwen capsules, but not Amoxicillin. I didn't remember until I got to the front door of their neighborhood. Fortunately, there are pharmacies near the entrance to their neighborhood, and Amoxicillin are everywhere.

When you're done, give her the pills. I hadn't gone far before I received her wechat message: "Is it still so terrible outside? I've stayed at home for so long, I'm so scared... "

At first, I didn't know how to comfort her. I'm not a comforter. But you have to comfort her. You have to respond.

And I said, "It's not that scary. You need to look at the right, authoritative information. Is it really that scary that I'm running around out there? "

From here on in, we've been talking on voice mail.

Last night she was asking me to buy her groceries. I also let her go on twitter to talk to my followers on twitter. In the process, I found that she was getting better and would make some jokes on Weibo.

A lot of the people who follow me on Weibo are from Wuhan, but most of them are from Hubei, really. I think it's good to make them laugh and relieve their mental stress, because a lot of people are under a lot of stress at this point.

Why do I say my psychological bearing capacity is strong? Because I took care of my father, who had an STD, for a month, and then he died. I've been there, I've been there. Let's say you break an arm and then when you put the bone in, it's stronger than it was before.

But a lot of people, especially young people, they've never experienced anything like this. Like the day a young man asked me to buy him pork floss and red bean bread, I remember thinking to myself, "what a young Master! " These young people had never experienced such a terrible state, plus they couldn't go out when they were locked up at home, what do you think that's like?

Many young people told me on Weibo, although he may not be tired, nor dangerous, but it is psychologically unbearable, I can understand. Including the young man who said I wanted red bean bread. I was a little angry, but I did my best to satisfy him, including when he told me later that he wanted fresh hot and dry noodles, which I understood. I told him later that I hadn't had hot and dry noodles for over a month either.

Fresh hot-dry noodles and bagged hot-dry noodles are two things, although both are called "hot-dry noodles" . I don't know if you can understand this, but people in Wuhan never eat hot and dry noodles in a bag, and neither do I.

What does fresh hot and dry noodles mean? It means something else. I get it.

In combination with my previous experiences, I have found that in this disaster, it may be the old who are the most vulnerable, physically and physically, but it is the young who are the most psychologically damaged.

6

Reasons for falling in love with Wuhan again

I now buy food, send food, basically do not earn money, sometimes also upside down.

That day someone gave me 500 yuan to buy fruit for the Guizhou medical team. I told the fruit shop owner, you help me to prepare 500 dollars of fruit, must be more than 500, especially 499,498,480 such. He hit 525(yuan) , after buying I give a person reimbursement. I mean, look, it's a picture of fruit and a receipt. He said he was GonNa pay me back, and I couldn't take it. You're GONNA charge me for this, aren't you? It can't be that precise, can it?

Today, too. When I said $1,000 worth of fruit, the boss gave me a $1,048. I patted the boss said, help me to make good, you do not give us Wuhan Shame. I mean, tell him not to act bad, you send someone a piece of bad fruit, what's that about? The boss is quite good, the fruit is really very good, also gave me a member price.

I said I came to Wuhan what is one of the reasons? It is called "self-salvation" , of course, a bit exaggerated, in fact, is a psychological self-healing process. I didn't ask for help with the whole thing. It was self-regulation. But this time, especially this month, it's been really good for me, you know?

The impact of the epidemic on the city of Wuhan was really huge, and I didn't understand why academician Zhong Nanshan wept and said Wuhan was "a city of heroes" . When I realized this, I went to Shouyi Square, and took pictures of Shouyi road and Shouyi Square. I said that there are so many roads in the world, and every road has a name, but only the name Shouyi, only Wuhan has it, only Wuhan has it. There are no other roads and squares in all of China with this name.

When you realize this problem, you find that Wuhan people suffer too much.

I always said I didn't like Wuhan, but when I said I didn't like Wuhan, it was like you and your mother were always fighting, your mother was always scolding you, but she was your mother, wasn't she? You may never say you love your mother, but you're stuck with Wuhan. Why didn't I say another city? Why?

I have also been looking for a reason to like Wuhan again, now to write the 5th, I strive to write it this year to 100.

The first is Hubei Province Bo, I particularly like Hubei Province Bo, have been to many times, this is why I came to Xudong, one is near Hubei Province Bo, and another is near Xudong Antique city.

Second, Wuhan often has some unexpected delicious things, such as roast goose rice, the boss is Hong Kong people, it seems, is called Hong Kong Lai Ji Roast Goose, especially delicious, of course, may be because I was hungry that day.

Third, from July until now, there have been lots of good things, such as a free taxi driver and hip aunts asking if you want some water.

What's number four? I can't remember.

Fifth is the Wuhan Yangtze River Bridge. The Wuhan Yangtze River Bridge is beautiful, beautiful.

I think, after such a huge trauma, all of these let me and Wuhan have a deeper feeling. It's like two people's relationship is going through a huge trial, and if you can survive that trial, your relationship is definitely going to be stronger, right?

After this time, I may be even more inseparable from Wuhan, because Wuhan has a special meaning to me, whether it is because of the epidemic itself, or because of the special time period here, I was in Wuhan special circumstances.

February 25,2020
